fields.Title: Siileng: ""You won't regret it, officer!" The..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You won't regret it, officer!" The street vendor smiles broadly.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Don't be shy, these are premium-cl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Don't be shy, these are premium-class clothes! Good quality fabrics, best retro design! Save the economy with your style, officer!"

fields.Title: Composure: "They itch. Like hell. Like an itch-..."
fields.Dialogue Text: They itch. Like hell. Like an itch-pit in hell.

fields.Title: You: ""Thanks for the advice, I'll try to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Thanks for the advice, I'll try to be more economically conscious."

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "How about some premium-class servic..."
fields.Dialogue Text: How about some premium-class service over here? Like paying with net worth. Go over and ask him if you can do that.

fields.Title: Pile of Clothes: "You find your hands deep in tattere..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You find your hands deep in tattered and faded garments made from weird polyester blends that make your body itch and sweat in all the wrong places.

fields.Title: You: ""This *economy* is really just a di..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This *economy* is really just a distraction from the cultural issues. You know -- *immigrants* and..."

fields.Title: You: ""Look man, I just want to buy some..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Look man, I just want to buy some clothes."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Doesn't matter," the street vendor..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Doesn't matter," the street vendor replies. "All that matters is the box. Check it out, officer."

fields.Title: You: ""Save the economy? What are you tal..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Save the economy? What are you talking about?"

fields.Title: Endurance: "This jacket is the apex of human ev..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This jacket is the apex of human evolution -- the moment at which man became weatherproof.

fields.Title: You: ""This doesn't make any sense. Why e..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This doesn't make any sense. Why exactly does the economy need saving?"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Is this really the economy we want..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Is this really the economy we want to leave to our children?"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""That's good, officer! That's exact..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's good, officer! That's exactly what the economy wants you to do."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""That's the spirit! We've all got t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's the spirit! We've all got to do our part. Your part is to open the box and buy some clothes."

fields.Title: Composure: "Something cold grazes your hand. Sy..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Something cold grazes your hand. Synthetic and sleek -- a windbreaker. 'SURF', it says, but also: 'WIND', 'SUMMER', '100% WATERPROOF', and 'SPORT'. All in different typefaces.

fields.Title: You: ""Those socialists in academia.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Those socialists in academia."

fields.Title: Shivers: "Practical, and yet it may deaden yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Practical, and yet it may deaden your senses to the world around you. Possibly because of the awful typeface.

fields.Title: You: ""But I don't have children. I think.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "But I don't have children. I think."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""I can't go extinct, officer! I've..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I can't go extinct, officer! I've got kids to feed. Once an economy goes extinct, it messes up the whole eco-system. You got to think about the consequences!"

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "If he really wants to save the econ..."
fields.Dialogue Text: If he really wants to save the economy he'd let you pay with net worth. Go over and ask him if you can

fields.Title: You: ""I want to buy the windbreaker.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I want to buy the windbreaker."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Economical, but also trendy!" the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Economical, but also trendy!" the street vendor shouts. "Look first-hand, buy second-hand. Keep the economy moving!"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Good choice, officer! Mega-sporty...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good choice, officer! Mega-sporty. And it's only 4.50 for you, sir!"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Oh." The street vendor pauses. "Lo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh." The street vendor pauses. "Look man, I'm not into *politics*. I like everyone. Check out the box!"

fields.Title: You: ""It's just nature: Powerful economi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's just nature: Powerful economies expand, weak economies go extinct."

fields.Title: Siileng: ""You keep coming back. That's good,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You keep coming back. That's good, officer! Keep browsing those clothes, keep saving that economy!"

fields.Title: You: "[Leave for now.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave for now.]

fields.Title: You: "Browse through the box."
fields.Dialogue Text: Browse through the box.

fields.Title: You: "Discard the woolly pants."
fields.Dialogue Text: Discard the woolly pants.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Look around, officer! You see all..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Look around, officer! You see all these premium goods, just sitting there, *not* getting bought? We've got to keep the flow of goods moving!"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""No luck?" the street vendor says,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No luck?" the street vendor says, visibly disappointed. "Why not take another look, officer? Keep supporting the economy!"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Haven't you heard, officer? We've..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Haven't you heard, officer? We've got to be economically conscious. Recycle your cash, keep it in circulation! Don't buy new things! Buy eco!"

fields.Title: You: ""You're right. We've got to save Mo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're right. We've got to save Mother Economy!"

fields.Title: You: ""And genetic atrophy.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "And genetic atrophy."

fields.Title: Half Light: "THE ITCH IS SO BAD YOU'LL WANT TO S..."
fields.Dialogue Text: THE ITCH IS SO BAD YOU'LL WANT TO SMASH SOMEONE'S FACE IN.

fields.Title: Pile of Clothes: "There are clothes inside. Cheap sec..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There are clothes inside. Cheap second-hand clothes, smelling of strangers' body odours.

fields.Title: Composure: "No good. All you can come up with a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No good. All you can come up with are some treated wool pants. You can tell they're too tight around your thighs and too loose around the waist.

fields.Title: Siileng: ""All natural materials, see?" The s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "All natural materials, see?" The street vendor interrupts, guiding your hand over the fabric. "Real wool, 100% skin-friendly! And they're yours for only 2 rel!"

fields.Title: Siileng: ""Too bad, officer. Kids make it all..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Too bad, officer. Kids make it all worthwhile. Without kids, who's going to be around to enjoy the economy?" He points at the clothes. "Don't let me stop you. Open the box and browse a little!"

fields.Title: Perception (Smell): "The box smells like cat piss -- or..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The box smells like cat piss -- or like an old person with no money.

fields.Title: You: "Touch them."
fields.Dialogue Text: Touch them.
